      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Soak the fruit, overnight",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine all the fruit and nut ingredients in a large bowl. Pour over the {{kirsch}}, stir well, cover, and leave overnight (or up to a week for deeper flavour).",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 150°C fan. Double-line the tin with baking paper on the base and sides. Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} and {{muscovado-dark}} together until combined, this is a dark, dense batter, not a pale cream. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time, then the {{black-treacle}}. Fold in the {{plain-flour}}, {{mixed-spice}}, {{ginger-ground}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Fold in all the soaked fruit. The mixture will be very stiff and dark.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, about 3 hours",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spoon into the tin and level the surface. Bake for approximately 3 hours. Cover the top with a double layer of baking paper after the first hour. The cake is done when a skewer comes out clean and the internal temperature reads 92°C. Cool completely in the tin. Poke holes all over with a skewer and pour 2 tablespoons of {{kirsch}} over the surface. Wrap tightly in greaseproof paper, then foil.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Feed the cake, weekly",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Unwrap the cake once a week and spoon 2 tablespoons of kirsch over the base. Re-wrap and return to the tin. This is ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "feeding a cake",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yft190000n8v4e01meuah"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": it preserves and flavours the crumb over the maturation period. Four weeks is the minimum; eight weeks gives a noticeably richer result.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Marzipan and ice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "One week before serving: mix the {{almond-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}} for the marzipan, and {{egg-whites}} for the marzipan to a smooth paste. Brush the cake with a little kirsch and press the marzipan over the top and sides. Leave uncovered for 24 hours to dry. Three days before serving: beat the {{egg-whites}} for the icing until frothy, then beat in the {{icing-sugar}} for the icing in stages until thick and glossy. Spread over the marzipan and leave to set hard.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
